balinese life, religion, festivals and offerings, architecture, music, dance, textiles, dress, carvings and paintings, masks, manuscripts, meals and much, much more. island of bali (periplus classics series), miguel covarrubias (author), adrian vickers (editor). when the mexican artist miguel covarrubias wrote his outsider's impression of balinese life and culture in 1937, he surely could not have imagined that well into the next century his work would still be considered the most authoritative text on the subject. absolutely vital reading, and it is astounding how little has changed in bali since the time this book was written. more on covarrubias' time in 